$interpreted: Ralph: ......
Hyde: *Chuckles* ...Come on~ Why so serious~
Hyde: The battle is about to reach its climax. If you don't start watching now, you're going to miss it!
？？？: As with the person monitoring you, we've already taken care of him for you.
？？？: ... Speak. So is this the same as the future you've observed?
Hyde: Angelia and Theodore beating the living hell out of each other in the desert?
Hyde: I've seen this scene so many times with this void disease-infected eye!
Hyde: In order to reach this ending, do you have any idea how much hard work I had to do behind the scenes!
Hyde: The two titans of the kingdom both perish on the same day. The sun will set and bring forth darkness.

Hyde: The blood of Vendacti's descendants will be offered as sacrifice to Sdorica. 
This a fabulous ending, isn't it!
Hyde: Here it comes... This is the final climax!

Theodore: Angelia, your resistance is futile!
You have no choice but to accept this ending.
Angelia: ......
Angelia: It seems that the threat of Rayzor and the nobles' unwillingness to help have indeed pushed uncle to the brink of desperation.
Theodore: What?
Officer: King Theodore! Bad news! The Bears and Sunshine Infantry have surrounded us and are fast approaching our position!
Dagger: Get 'em!!
Dagger: Been standing by at that sand dune for forever! Finally, I get to kick human butt!
Dagger: Hmph! Payback time for everything you people did to us before!
Dagger: KILL!!!
Theodore: Angelia! How did you...
Angelia: ... The basis of all strategies is to rely on the information you collected, then simulate and predict your opponent's tactics.
Angelia: As well as let your opponent misjudge the information and the leverage you have.

Angelia: When news broke that I was the one in possession of Rayzor, you had to try and be a step ahead. Your prediction of me is most certainly: 
"Now that the secret is out, I have to leave Atlas and retreat back to Sunshine Infantry as soon as possible."
Naya: If we were able to bring Rayzor's core back, the tide of the war would turn against you.
Naya: So, intercepting us during our return became your only viable option.
Angelia: In addition, of the roads between Sunshine Infantry and Atlas, this is the only place where you have a chance of intercepting us.
Angelia: Therefore, I requested Sir Dagger to prepare an ambush long before our arrival.

Naya: Once they saw Rayzor being fired, those cowardly nobles would be too scared to lend you any troops. 
Without their help, this battle becomes a simple case of your men against all of us!
Theodore: ......
Dagger: Why bother talking so much? Time to fight!
Hyde: W... What...?

？？？: The tide is gradually turning against Theodore. 
Is this part of your calculations as well?
Hyde: Wait... It can't be... I never taught her anything like this. Those armies too; without my command, how did they... That's not possible...
Tica: Tada~ Say hello to Team Tica Version 2.0!

Tica: Let me make things clear first! The Academy does require us to maintain a neutral position. 
B-U-T, I'm on my academic break right now.

Tica: I'm using my private time to accept a personal request from my adorable junior Leah. That's why I'm here, to help her out.
Therefore~ you better not be a tattletale and report me to Headmaster Ceres~
Hyde: You people... why are you here?
Lio: Sis Angel has asked me in private to monitor and investigate the people in the Infantry. She wanted to find the spy who leaked our strategies.
Leah: The princess gave him this long list of names. It contains pretty much everyone in the Infantry, and she wanted Lio to investigate them one by one.
Leah: If not for the sheer amount of names, I wouldn't have interfered to help him out, or even went as far as asking sis Tica for help.

Hyde: Didn't she ask me to find out who the spy is?
Yet she secretly asked you to do it as well... 
So she is suspicious about me from the start?
Hyde: Impossible, I should've gotten her full-fledged trust already!

Lio: Sis Angel said that this is what you taught her:
"Have faith in your decisions; have doubt for everything else."
Lio: If you're clean, naturally, you won't be afraid of an investigation...
Leah: If we didn't see you kill those two soldiers back at Totemtaff, we would've put you on the "clean" list a long time ago!

Hyde: Hahaha... I certainly didn't expect this.
She got a brat I completely ignored to keep an eye on me?
Hyde: That princess... so she has mastered everything I taught her...
Hyde: However, with just you three, do you have what it takes to alter the future I saw!
Tica: Hehe, V for Victory~!
Hyde: It's not over. I'll...
Hyde: ... Ugh!?
？？？: Hyde, are you alright?
Hyde: Ugh... This scenery, why...
Tica: Huh? What? Hello? What did you just saw?
Hyde: Haha, if this is how the future will turn out, then I guess it's quite interesting too!
Hyde: Everyone! It's time for a prediction from the one-and-only Hyde Oust!
Hyde: Congratulations, the princess will emerge as the final victor of this war~
Hyde: However, that princess, she'll do some terrible things later. If you still want to live, you better leave her side as quickly as possible~
Lio: Liar! I won't allow you to speak bad things about sis Angel!
Leah: That's right! What did you see exactly! Explain yourself!
Hyde: The future I saw? That's...
Hyde: ... a secret for you to find out~
